 Abu Darda, may Allah be pleased with him, passed by\u00a0a man who was being beaten because of his sin and they were cursing\u00a0him. Abu Darda\u00a0said, \u201cWhat do you think if he had fallen into a well. Would you not try to rescue him?\u201d They said yes.\u00a0Abu Darda\u00a0said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35393,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/03\/16\/abu-darda-sabr\/","url_meta":{"origin":30966,"position":1},"title":"Abu Darda on Patience: Be forbearing in the face of insults, curses","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 16, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdur Rahman ibn Jubayr reported: Abu Darda, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cGive up your reputation for the sake of Allah. Whoever abuses you, insults you, or fights you, leave him to Allah. If you do a bad deed, then ask forgiveness from Allah.\u201d Source: Ta\u0304ri\u0304kh Dimashq 47\/180\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32689,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/06\/abu-darda-act-upon-knowledge\/","url_meta":{"origin":30966,"position":2},"title":"Abu Darda on Judgment: Did you not act upon your knowledge?","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 6, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Luqman reported: Abu Darda, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, I fear from my Lord on the Day of Resurrection that I will be called in front of the heads of all creation, saying: O \u2018Uwaymir! I will say: At your service, my Lord. He will say: Did\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":31,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/09\/14\/curses-not-intercessors\/","url_meta":{"origin":30966,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Curses: Habitual cursers will not be intercessors","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 14, 2010","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Darda reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThose in the habit of cursing others will not be intercessors or witnesses on the Day of Resurrection.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2595 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064e\u0651\u0631\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0627\u0621\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14675,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/06\/09\/unjust-curse-backfires\/","url_meta":{"origin":30966,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Cursing: Unjust curse backfires against accuser","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 9, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Darda reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVer